To run nexus as a container:
- docker engine must be running 
- java must be running   

Install docker engine: 
- Become root
  sudo -i
  
- Update your server 
  apt update

- Upgrade your server packages 
  apt upgrade

- Install Java as a prerequisite 
  apt install default-jre -y

- Update your server 
  apt update

- Install Docker   
  apt install docker.io -y
  chmod 666 /var/run/docker.sock
  systemctl enable docker 
  systemctl start docker
  #systemctl status docker

- Create a nexus user  
  adduser nexus  

- Add nexus to the docker group 
  usermod -aG docker nexus  

- Allow the nexus user to run all commands with sudo without password.
  echo "nexus   ALL=(ALL)       NOPASSWD: ALL" > /etc/sudoers.d/nexus

- Become nexus user  
  su - nexus  

- Install nexus  
  docker pull sonatype/nexus3
  docker run -d -p 8081:8081 --name nexus sonatype/nexus3
  systemctl enable nexus  
  systemctl start nexus   
  #systemctl status nexus   

- Check on browser  
  curl ifconfig.co 
  #IP/port 
  # Default port is 8081 
  # Default user is admin 
  # Default password 
    - Get into the nexus container  
      docker exec -it containerID or containerName /bin/bash  
    - Get the password 
      cat admin.password
